Reed Exhibitions Africa has confirmed that Game of Thrones star Jason Momoa will attend Comic Con Africa as a special guest. Momoa is known for his roles as Khal Drogo in Game of Thrones, and Aquaman in Justice League. He also stars in the Netflix series Frontier and will reprise his role as Aquaman in a standalone film – which will premiere later this year. Comic Con Africa will showcase comic books, films, and series, as well as a large range of pop culture and entertainment elements – including animation, toys, gadgets, and gaming. It will be held from 14-16 September 2018 at the Kyalami Grand Prix Circuit & International Convention Centre. Momoa will be in attendance on 15 and 16 September.